   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2800_1.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>THE DUCHESS OF HAMILTON. 19, S<hi rend="superscript">T</hi> JAMES'
                     SQUARE, S.W.1.</addrLine>
               </address>


               <dateline>
                  <date when="1922-07-03">
                     <hi rend="underline">3<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi> July 1922</hi>
                  </date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>Dear Sir Thomas Hardy.</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I have not the pleasure of knowing you personally, but have I think read with much
               enjoyment all your books.</p>

            <p>I do hope you are interested in a reform to do away with the present horrible <pb
                  n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2800_2.jpg"/> methods of killing animals for food.</p>

            <p>I do not suppose you can come to the meetings, but do please send us a message of
               encouragement.</p>

            <closer>
               <salute>Believe me</salute>
               <salute>Yours sincerely</salute>
               <signed>
                  <hi rend="underline">Nina Hamilton</hi>
               </signed>
            </closer>


         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
